==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subsecute
<hw>Sub"se*cute</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subsecutus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>subsequi</ets>. See
<er>Subsequent</er>.]</ety> <def>To follow closely, or so as to
overtake; to pursue.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To follow and detain him, if by any possibility he could be
<qex>subsecuted</qex> and overtaken.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subsecutive</ent>⟦br⟧
